                                                   Gazza held 
                      
	London: Former England midfielder Paul Gascoigne is being held under the Mental Health Act, a police source said on Thursday.         
	The former Tottenham Hotspur and Newcastle United player, widely known as Gazza, was arrested at the Hilton Hotel in Gateshead, on Wednesday evening.         
	Nobody was injured and there was no violence and no damage to the hotel.           (REUTERS)                                                                                                                   
